# Console Command Documentation

Whenever you add, rename, remove, or change a controller-node console/terminal
command, update the docs in the **same change**. Treat `docs/console.md` as the
authoritative operator reference.

This applies to:

- A new/changed `esp_console_cmd_t` (e.g. the `lo-*` helpers in
  `led_orchestra_console.cpp`) — its name, arguments, and behavior.
- A new built-in command group registered in `app_main.cpp` (controller,
  ot_cli, diagnostics, etc.).
- New/changed cluster command ids, tags, or effect ids in
  `common/led_orchestra_matter.h` and `cluster/led-orchestra.md`.

When changing a command, also update, as needed:

- `docs/console.md` — operator-facing command list, arguments, and flow.
- `matter-prototype/cluster/led-orchestra.md` — the field/tag contract.
- `matter-prototype/controller-node/README.md` — the implemented-slice list.

## Example

Adding `lo-list-nodes` to `led_orchestra_console.cpp` requires, in the same
change, a new entry under "LED Orchestra Commands" in `docs/console.md` with its
arguments and behavior, plus the README implemented-slice bullet. Do not leave
the command undocumented.
